two ships you are curious about but haven't actually started shipping:

13. Mouth and Brooke
14. Burke and Izzie

1.) Why do you dislike #11 so much? 

Idk, they have just never been my favorite. I thought it was wrong for them to make her start having feelings for him when her husband was away in Iraq. They just never were one of those couples that I wished would get together and they just do nothing for me.

2.) Who is someone you know that ships #13? 

I actually don't know anyone that ships them.

3.) What would be your ideal scenario for couple #3 (even if the show isn't on the air anymore)? 

Um, when he came back into the show last season I wanted her to realize that Logan wasn't the right person for her and she has been in love with Jess the whole time. She was just kidding herself with all these other guys and that there was always something missing in her other relationships and the reason for that is because none of them were him. *sigh*


4.) Which is your favorite episode for #1? Try to pick just one, if you can. 

Toss up between the Pilot and 3.16. In the pilot, it was all about them. I mean Peyton was with Nathan, but the connection between them was too intense for words right from the beginning. Then in 3.16, the kiss -thud- It gave me the hope I needed to know that LP wasn't forgotten by Mark Schwann. And that kiss was the sweetest kiss in all TV history. (I totally agree Christina) =] No need to change that answer... 

5.) How long have you been following couple #6? 

From the beginning. They were always friends and they always had that connection, you could see it everytime they looked at each other. You could tell from the first episode that they were going to end up loving each other and they'd be the end game.

6.) What's the story with #8? What made you stop liking them/caring?
